The ZDAO contract is designed to be a bare bones, minimalistic approach to a versitile DAO structure. The ZDAO is designed to
work with other contracts including other zer0 based contracts AND approved non-zer0 based contracts.*

constructor.details: this function automatically deploys a rep token for the DAO if the _existingToken param is set to the 0x0 address

params._daoName: is the name of the zDAO
params._existingToken: is the address of an existing ERC20 the DAO will use as a rep token(If applicable)
params._proposalTime: is the time in seconds that a proposal will be active for*
params._quorum: is the minimum percentage of voteWeight needed for a vote to pass
params._tokenName: is the name of the DAO's rep token(if applicable)
params._tokenSym: is the symbol of the DAO's rep token(if applicable)
params._transferableRep: is a bool representing whether or not a DAO's rep token can be transfered from one account to another

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

vote(uint256,bool).details: this function will trigger the _checkThreshold function which determines if enough members have voted to fire the executeVote function.*

params._ProposalID: is the number ID associated with the particular proposal the user wishes to vote on
params.supportsProposal: is a bool value(true or false) representing whether or not a member supports a proposal -true if they do support the proposal -false if they do not support the proposal

methods.constructor: the constructor function is fired only once during contract creation and is used to set up the zDAO
